column1: What are the names, countries for every singer in descending order of age?
column2: select name, country from singer order by birthday desc
column3: new_concert_singer | select name, country from singer order by birthday asc

column1: What is the average, minimum, and maximum id of all French singers?
column2: select avg(singer_id), min(singer_id), max(singer_id) from singer where country = 'F'
column3: new_concert_singer | select avg(singer_id), min(singer_id), max(singer_id) from singer where country = 'France'

column1: What is the average, minimum, and maximum id for French singers?
column2: select avg(singer_id), min(singer_id), max(singer_id) from singer where country = 'F'
column3: new_concert_singer | select avg(singer_id), min(singer_id), max(singer_id) from singer where country = 'France'

column1: List all song names by singers above the average age.
column2: select song_name from singer where birthday > (select avg(birthday) from singer)
column3: new_concert_singer | select song_name from singer where birthday < (select avg(birthday) from singer)

column1: What are all the song names by singers who are older than average?
column2: select song_name from singer where birthday > (select avg(birthday) from singer)
column3: new_concert_singer | select song_name from singer where birthday < (select avg(birthday) from singer)

column1: How many concerts are there after or in year 2014?
column2: select count(*) from concert where year > 2014
column3: new_concert_singer | select count(*) from concert where year >= 2014

column1: How many concerts occurred after or in 2014?
column2: select count(*) from concert where year > 2014
column3: new_concert_singer | select count(*) from concert where year >= 2014

column1: What is the name and highest attendance of the stadium  with the most concerts after 2013?
column2: select t2.name, t2.highest, t2.average from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year > 2013 group by t1.stadium_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.name, t2.capacity from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year >= 2014 group by t2.stadium_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which concert is the oldest?
column2: select concert_name, year from concert order by year desc limit 1
column3: new_concert_singer | select concert_name from concert order by year asc limit 1

column1: Show the highest attendance without any concert.
column2: select highest from stadium
column3: new_concert_singer | select highest from stadium where stadium_id not in (select stadium_id from concert)

column1: Show countries where a singer born in 1981 or 1991 are from.
column2: select country from singer where birthday like "1981" or birthday like "911"
column3: new_concert_singer | select country from singer where birthday like '1981%' or birthday like '1991%'

column1: List all singer names in concerts after or in year 2014.
column2: select t3.name from singer_in_concert as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.concert_id = t2.concert_id join singer as t3 on t1.singer_id = t3.singer_id where t2.year > 2014
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.name from singer_in_concert as t1 join singer as t2 on t1.singer_id = t2.singer_id join concert as t3 on t1.concert_id = t3.concert_id where t3.year >= 2014

column1: What are the names of the singers who performed in a concert before or in 2014?
column2: select t3.name from singer_in_concert as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.concert_id = t2.concert_id join singer as t3 on t1.singer_id = t3.singer_id where t2.year < 2014
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.name from singer_in_concert as t1 join singer as t2 on t1.singer_id = t2.singer_id join concert as t3 on t1.concert_id = t3.concert_id where t3.year <= 2014

column1: Find the lowest and highest attendance of the stadiums which some concerts happened in the years of both 2014 and 2015.
column2: select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.name, t2.location from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015

column1: What are the lowest and highest attendance of the stadiums that had concerts that occurred in both 2014 and 2015?
column2: select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.name, t2.location from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015

column1: Find the weight of the youngest dog.
column2: select weight from pets order by birthdate asc limit 1
column3: new_pets_1 | select weight from pets order by birthdate desc limit 1

column1: Find the number of puppy pets that are raised by female students (with sex F).
column2: select count(*) from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid join student as t3 on t1.stuid = t3.stuid where t3.sex = 'F'
column3: new_pets_1 | select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t1.sex = 'F' and t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: How many puppy pets are raised by female students?
column2: select count(*) from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid join student as t3 on t1.stuid = t3.stuid where t3.sex = 'F'
column3: new_pets_1 | select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t1.sex = 'F' and t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: Find the first name of students who have kitten or puppy pet.
column2: select t2.fname from has_pet as t1 join student as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t1.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'kitten' or t3.pettype = 'puppy'
column3: new_pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat' or t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: What are the first names of every student who has a kitten or puppy as a pet?
column2: select t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'kitten' or t3.pettype = 'puppy'
column3: new_pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat' or t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: Find the major and age of students who do not have a kitten pet.
column2: select major, age from student except select t1.major, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t2.petid in (select stuid from has_pet as t3 join pets as t4 on t3.petid = t4.petid where t4.pettype = 'kitten')
column3: new_pets_1 | select major, age from student where stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What major is every student who does not own a kitten as a pet, and also how old are they?
column2: select major, age from student where stuid not in (select stuid from has_pet)
column3: new_pets_1 | select major, age from student where stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: Find the id of students who do not have a kitten pet.
column2: select stuid from student except select stuid from has_pet where petid in (select petid from pets where pettype = 'kitten')
column3: new_pets_1 | select stuid from student except select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: What are the ids of the students who do not own kittens as pets?
column2: select stuid from student except select stuid from has_pet where petid in (select petid from pets where pettype = 'kitten')
column3: new_pets_1 | select stuid from student except select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: Find the first name and age of students who have a dog but do not have a puppy as a pet.
column2: select fname, age from student where stuid not in (select stuid from has_pet where pettype = 'dog'
column3: new_pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What is the first name of every student who has a puppy but does not have a kitten?
column2: select t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.sex = "M" and t2.petid not in (select t1.stuid from has_pet as t3 join pets as t4 on t3.petid = t4.petid where t4.pettype = "dog" or t4.pettype = "kitten")
column3: new_pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: Find the id and weight of all pets older than that born in 2020.
column2: select petid, weight from pets where birthdate > 2020
column3: new_pets_1 | select petid, weight from pets where birthdate < '2020-01-01'

column1: Find the name and age of students who have a pet.
column2: select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid
column3: new_pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname, t1.lname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid

column1: What are the different names and ages of the students who do have pets?
column2: select distinct t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid
column3: new_pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname, t1.lname t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid

column1: How many countries does each continent have? List the continent id, continent name and the number of countries.
column2: select t1.continent, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.continent = t2.continent group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: For each continent, list its id, name, and how many countries it has?
column2: select continent, countryname, count(*) from countries group by continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: How many models does each car maker produce? List maker full name, id and the number.
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: What is the full name of each car maker, along with its id and how many models it produces?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: Which model of the car has the minimum horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: What is the model of the car with the smallest amount of horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: Find the model of the car whose weight is below the average weight.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: What is the model for the car with a weight smaller than the average?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: Find the name of the makers that produced some cars in the past two years?
column2: select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model join cars_data as t4 on t3.makeid = t4.id where t4.year >= '2019';

column1: Find the make and production time of the cars that were produced in the earliest year?
column2: select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid order by t1.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: What is the maker of the carr produced in the earliest year and what year was it?
column2: select t1.maker, t2.year from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id order by t2.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: Which distinct car models are the produced before or in 1980?
column2: select distinct model from model_list where modelid not in (select id from cars_data where year < 1980)
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year <= 1980;

column1: What are the different models for the cards produced before or in 1980?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.year < 1980
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year <= 1980;

column1: How many car makers are there in each continents? List the continent name and the count.
column2: select t2.continent, count(*) from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: What is the name of each continent and how many car makers are there in each one?
column2: select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.continent = t2.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: How many car models are produced by each maker? List the count and the maker full name.

column3: car_1 | select count(*), t2.fullname, t2.id from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.id;

column1: What is the number of car models that are produced by each maker and what is the id and full name of each maker?
column2: select count(*), t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname!= "id" group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select count(*), t2.fullname, t2.id from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.id;

column1: How many car models are produced in the america?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.country = 'USA'
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What is the count of the car models produced in the United States?

column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What is the smallest weight of the car produced with 8 cylinders on 1974?
column2: select min(weight) from cars_data where cylinders = 8 and year = 1974
column3: car_1 | select weight from cars_data where cylinders = 4 and year = 1974 order by weight asc limit 1;

column1: What is the minimu weight of the car with 8 cylinders produced in 1974?
column2: select min(weight) from cars_data where year = 1974 and cylinders = 8
column3: car_1 | select weight from cars_data where cylinders = 4 and year = 1974 order by weight asc limit 1;

column1: What are the countries having at least one car maker? List name and id.

column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What are the names and ids of all countries with at least one car maker?

column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: Which European countries have at least 3 car manufacturers?

column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What are the names of all European countries with at least 3 manufacturers?
column2: select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t1.country having count(*) >= 3

column1: What is the largest amount of horsepower for the models with 3 cylinders and what make is it?
column2: select max(horsepower) from cars_data where cylinders = 3 intersect select make from car_names group by make having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.

column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the average horsepower of the cars before or in 1980?
column2: select avg(horsepower) from cars_data where year < 1980
column3: car_1 | select avg(horsepower) from cars_data where year <= 1980;

column1: What is the average horsepower for all cards produced before or in 1980?

column1: What is the average edispl of the cars of model tesla?

column3: car_1 | select avg(t2.edispl) from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t1.model = 'tesla';

column1: What is the average edispl for all teslas?

column3: car_1 | select avg(t2.edispl) from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t1.model = 'tesla';

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: how many cars were produced in the last two years?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where year = (select max(year) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where year >= 2019;

column1: In the last two years, how many cars were made?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where year = (select max(year) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where year >= 2019;

column1: How many car models were produced by American Motor?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.maker = "American Motor"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What is the number of car models created by American Motor?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.maker = "American Motor"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What are the names and ids of all makers with more than 3 models?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.i

column1: Tell me the owner id and last name of the owner who spent the most on treatments of his or her dogs.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t3.dog_id = t2.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which owner has paid the largest amount of money in total for their dogs? Show the owner id and zip code.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t2.charge_amount
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1

column1: Find the owner id and zip code of the owner who spent the most money in total for his or her dogs.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t2.cost_of_treatment
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1

column1: Which professionals have done at least two types of treatments? List the professional id and name.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.first_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.professional_id, t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: Find the id and home and phone number of the professionals who operate two or more types of treatments.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.home_phone, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.professional_id, t1.home_phone, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: What are the name of the professionals who have done treatment with cost below average?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t2.cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments)
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )

column1: Which professionals have operated a treatment that costs less than the average? Give me their names.
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments)
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )

column1: List the date of each treatment, together with the name of the professional who operated it.
column2: select date_of_treatment, t3.first_name, t3.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id join treatment_types as
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.date_of_treatment, t2.first_name, t2.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id

column1: List pairs of the owner's names and the dogs's name.
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join dogs as t3 on t1.dog_id = t3.dog_id
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t1.last_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id

column1: What are each owner's name and their dogs's name?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join breeds as t3 on t1.breed_code = t3.breed_code
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t1.last_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id

column1: List the names of the dogs of the rarest breed and the treatment dates of them.
column2: select t2.name, t1.date_of_treatment from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t2.breed_code = (select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) desc limit 1)
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.name, t2.date_of_treatment from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.breed_code = ( select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) asc limit 1 )

column1: Which dogs are of the rarest breed? Show their names and treatment dates.
column2: select name, date_of_treatment from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t2.breed_code = (select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) desc limit 1)
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.name, t2.date_of_treatment from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.breed_code = ( select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) asc limit 1 )

column1: Which dogs are owned by someone who lives in VA? List the owner's first name and the dog's name.
column2: select first_name, name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'VA'
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: Find the first names of owners living in VA and the names of dogs they own.
column2: select t2.first_name, t3.name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join dogs as t3 on t1.dog_id = t3.dog_id where t2.state = 'VA'
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: What is the treatment date from dog arriving to departing?
column2: select t1.date_of_treatment from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id order by t2.date_arrived - t2.date_departed
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.date_arrived, t1.date_departed from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id

column1: Find the dog treatment period from arriving to departing date.
column2: select date_of_treatment, date_arrived from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id order by t2.date_arrived, t2.date_departed
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.date_arrived, t1.date_departed from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id

column1: List the last name of the owner owning the youngest dog.
column2: select t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id order by t1.age asc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: Who owns the youngest dog? Give me his or her last name.
column2: dog
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: List the emails of the professionals who live in the state of HI or WI.

column3: dog_kennels | select email_address from professionals where state = 'Hawaii' or state = 'Wisconsin'

column1: What are the emails of the professionals living in either the state of HI or WI?
column2: select email_address from professionals where state = "HI" or state = "WI"
column3: dog_kennels | select email_address from professionals where state = 'Hawaii' or state = 'Wisconsin'

column3: dog_kennels | select count(*) from dogs where abandoned_yn = 1 and age < ( select avg(age) from dogs )

column1: What is the name and nationality of origin of every musicians who has a song with the word 'Hey' in its title?

column1: What are the number of musical performances that occurred in the stadium with the largest number of seats?

column1: Find the number of puppies that are raised by female students (with gender F).
column2: select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.sex = "F"
column3: pets_1 | select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t1.sex = 'F' and t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: How many puppies are raised by female students?
column2: select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.sex = 'F'
column3: pets_1 | select count(*) from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t1.sex = 'F' and t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: Find the given name of students who have kitten or puppy pet.
column2: select t2.fname from has_pet as t1 join student as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t1.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'kitten' or t3.pettype = 'puppy'
column3: pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat' or t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: What are the given names of every student who has a kitten or puppy as a pet?
column2: select t1.fname, t1.lname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'kitten' or t3.pettype = 'puppy'
column3: pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat' or t3.pettype = 'dog'

column1: Find the major and age of students who do not have a kitten pet.
column2: select major, age from student except select t1.major, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t2.petid in (select stuid from has_pet as t3 join pets as t4 on t3.petid = t4.petid where t4.pettype = 'kitten')
column3: pets_1 | select major, age from student where stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What discipline is every student who does not own a kitten as a pet, and also how old are they?
column2: select major, age from student where stuid not in (select stuid from has_pet)
column3: pets_1 | select major, age from student where stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: Find the id of students who do not have a kitten pet.
column2: select stuid from student except select stuid from has_pet where petid in (select petid from pets where pettype = 'kitten')
column3: pets_1 | select stuid from student except select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: What are the ids of the students who do not own kittens as pets?
column2: select stuid from student except select stuid from has_pet where petid in (select petid from pets where pettype = 'kitten')
column3: pets_1 | select stuid from student except select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: Find the given name and age of students who have a puppy but do not have a cat as a pet.
column2: select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.sex = "M" and t2.petid!= "cat"
column3: pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What is the given name of every student who has a dog but does not have a kitten?
column2: select fname from student where stuid in (select t1.stuid from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid where t2.pettype = 'dog' except select t1.stuid from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid where t2.pettype = 'kitten')
column3: pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What is the average and maximum age for each pet species?
column2: select pet_age, avg(pet_age), max(pet_age) from pets group by pettype
column3: pets_1 | select avg(pet_age), max(pet_age), pettype from pets group by pettype

column1: What are the different given names and ages of the students who do have pets?
column2: select distinct t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t2.petid in (select t1.stuid from has_pet as t3 join student as t4 on t3.stuid = t4.stuid)
column3: pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid

column1: Find the id of the animals owned by student whose family name is 'Smith'.

column3: pets_1 | select t2.petid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.lname = 'Smith'

column1: What is the id of the animals owned by the student whose family name is 'Smith'?
column2: select t2.petid from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid join student as t3 on t1.stuid = t3.stuid where t3.fname = "Smith"
column3: pets_1 | select t2.petid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid where t1.lname = 'Smith'

column1: Find the family name of the student who has a kitten that is age 3.
column2: select t2.fname, t2.lname from has_pet as t1 join student as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t1.petid = t3.petid where t2.age = 3
column3: pets_1 | select t1.lname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pet_age = 3 and t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: What is the family name of the student who has a kitten that is 3 years old?

column3: pets_1 | select t1.lname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pet_age = 3 and t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: How many States does each continent have? List the continent id, continent name and the number of nations.

column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: For each continent, list its id, name, and how many States it has?
column2: select t1.continent, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.continent = t2.continent group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: How many models does each car manufacturer produce? List manufacturer full name, id and the number.

column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: What is the full name of each car manufacturer, along with its id and how many models it produces?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: Which model of the vehicle has the minimum horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: What is the model of the vehicle with the smallest amount of power?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: Find the model of the vehicle who is lighter than the average.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: What is the model for the vehicle with a weight smaller than the average?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: Find the name of the manufacturer that produced some vehicles in the year of 1970?
column2: select t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid join cars_data as t3 on t3.id = t2.makeid where t3.year = 1970
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model join cars_data as t4 on t3.makeid = t4.id where t4.year = '1970';

column1: What is the name of the different car manufacturers who produced a vehicle in 1970?
column2: select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.year = 1970
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model join cars_data as t4 on t3.makeid = t4.id where t4.year = '1970';

column1: Find the make and production time of the vehicles that were produced in the earliest year?
column2: select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid order by t1.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: What is the manufacturer of the vehicle produced in the earliest year and what year was it?
column2: select t1.maker, t2.year from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id order by t2.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: Which distinct vehicle models are the produced after 1980?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.year > 1980
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year > 1980;

column1: What are the different models for the vehicles produced after 1980?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.year > 1980
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year > 1980;

column1: How many car manufacturers are there in each continents? List the continent name and the count.
column2: select t2.continent, count(*) from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.continent group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: What is the name of each continent and how many vehicle manufacturers are there in each one?
column2: select count(*), continent from continents group by continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: Which of the States has the most car manufacturers? List the State name.
column2: select t1.country from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t1.country order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t1.country order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What is the number of vehicle models that are produced by each manufacturer and what is the id and full name of each manufacturer?
column2: select count(*), t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select count(*), t2.fullname, t2.id from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.id;

column1: How many French car manufacturers are there?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers where country = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: What is the number of manufacturers of vehicle in France?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers where country = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: How many vehicle models are produced in the usa?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.country = "USA"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What is the count of the vehicle models produced in the United States?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.country = "United States"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What are the States having at least one vehicle manufacturer? List name and id.
column2: car_
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What are the names and ids of all States with at least one vehicle manufacturer?
column2: select t2.countryname, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: Which States in europe have at least 3 vehicle manufacturers?
column2: select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t2.countryid having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What are the names of all European States with at least 3 manufacturers?
column2: select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t2.countryid having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What is the maximum power and the manufacturer of the vehicle models with 3 cylinders?
column2: select max(horsepower), t2.maker from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: What is the largest amount of power for the models with 3 cylinders and what manufacturer is it?
column2: select max(horsepower), t2.maker from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the automobile model with the highest mpg?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the average edispl for all volvos?
column2: select avg(edispl) from cars_data where id = "volvo"
column3: car_1 | select avg(t2.edispl) from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t1.model = 'volvo';

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of automobiles?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: How many automobile models were produced by the manufacturer with full name American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What is the number of automobile models created by the car manufacturer American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.maker = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What are the names and ids of all manufacturers with more than 3 models?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: Which distinctive types are produced by manufacturer with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t1.make from car_names as t1 join car_makers as t2 on
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different models created by either the car manufacturer General Motors or weighed more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.makeid where t2.make = 'General Motors' union select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.makeid where
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: In which years automobiles were produced weighing no less than 3000 and no more than 4000?
column2: select year from cars_data where weight <= 3000 and weight > 4000
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.year from cars_data as t1 where t1.weight > 3000 and t1.weight < 4000;

column1: What are the different years in which there were vehicles produced that weighed less than 4000 and also vehicles that weighted more than 3000?
column2: select distinct year from cars_data where weight < 4000 intersect select distinct year from cars_data where weight > 3000
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.year from cars_data as t1 where t1.weight > 3000 and t1.weight < 4000;

column1: What is the power of the automobile with the largest accelerate?
column2: car_
column3: car_1 | select t1.horsepower from cars_data as t1 order by t1.accelerate desc limit 1;

column1: For model volvo, how many cylinders does the automobile with the least accelerate have?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.make = 'Volvo' order by t1.accelerate limit 1
column3: car_1 | select count(cylinders) from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'volvo' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: For a volvo model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select cylinders from cars_data where accelerate = (select min(accelerate) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(cylinders) from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'volvo' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many automobiles have a larger accelerate than the automobile with the largest power?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of automobiles with a greater accelerate than the one with the most power?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(accelerate) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: For the automobiles with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest power?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: For all of the 4 cylinder automobiles, which model has the most power?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the automobiles with more than lowest power, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the vehicle makeid and manufacturer name.
column2: select t1.makeid, t1.maker from car_names as t2 join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t1.id
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the automobiles that do not have the minimum power, what are the manufacturer ids and names of al those with less than 4 cylinders?
column2: select t1.maker, t2.make from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where 4 = (select min(horsepower), t2.makeid from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.cylinders < 4)
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders < 4;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
column2: select model from model_list where weight < 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor Company?
column2: select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.weight < 3500 except select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.id
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the automobile manufacturers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 automobile manufacturers? List the id and the manufacturer.
column2: select t1.maker, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and manufacturers of all automobile manufacturers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 automobiles?
column2: select t1.maker, t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.maker, t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the nations which have more than 3 vehicle manufacturers or produce the 'fiat' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.maker group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: What are the ids and names of all States that either have more than 3 automobile manufacturers or produce fiats?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country where t2.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name = 'Timmothy' and last_name = 'Ward'

column1: Who is the first student to register? List the given name, middle name and family name.
column2: select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered asc limit 1

column1: What is the given, middle, and family name of the first student to register?
column2: select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered asc limit 1

column1: Who is the earliest graduate of the school? List the given name, middle name and family name.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.f
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_left asc limit 1

column1: What is the given, middle, and family name of the earliest school graduate?
column2: select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered - date_left
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_left asc limit 1

column1: Whose permanent address is different from his or her current address? List his or her given name.
column2: select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: What is the given name of the student whose permanent address is different from his or her current one?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.address_id!= t1.current_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: Which place holds the most number of students currently? List the place id and all lines.
column2: select t1.address_id, t1.line_1 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.address_id, t1.line_1, t1.line_2 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: On average, when were the student record printed?
column2: select avg(date_first_registered) from students
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select avg(transcript_date) from transcripts

column1: What is the average student record date?
column2: select avg(date_first_registered) from students
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select avg(transcript_date) from transcripts

column1: When is the first student record released? List the date and details.
column2: select date_first_registered, other_student_details from students
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select transcript_date, other_details from transcripts order by transcript_date asc limit 1

column1: What is the last student record release date?
column2: select max(date_left) from students
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select transcript_date from transcripts order by transcript_date desc limit 1

column1: When was the last student record released?
column2: select max(date_first_registered) from students
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select transcript_date from transcripts order by transcript_date desc limit 1

column1: How many times at most can a curriculum enrollment result show in different student records? Also show the curriculum enrollment id.
column2: select count(*), t1.course_id from student_enrolment_courses as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_enrolment_id = t2.student_enrolment_id group by t1.course_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the maximum number of times that a curriculum shows up in different student records and what is that curriculum's enrollment id?
column2: select count(*), t1.student_enrolment_id from student_enrolment as t1 join courses as t2 on t1.student_enrolment_id = t2.course_id group by t1.student_enrolment_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Show the date of the student record which shows the least number of results, also list the id.
column2: select t1.date_first_registered, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1

column1: What is the date and id of the student record with the least number of results?
column2: select t1.date_first_registered, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1

column1: Find the academic session when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.
column2: select t1.semester_id from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id where t2.student_id = 'Master' intersect select t1.semester_id from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id where t2.student_id = 'Bache'
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What is the id of the academic session that had both Masters and Bachelors students enrolled?
column2: select semester_id from student_enrolment where student_id in (select student_id from student_enrolment where degree_program_id = 'Masters' intersect select student_id from student_enrolment where degree_program_id = 'Bachelor')
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What are the different places that have students living there?
column2: select distinct t1.city from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(distinct current_address_id) from students

column1: List all the student particulars in reversed lexicographical order.
column2: select distinct first_name, last_name from students order by other_student_details desc
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select other_student_details from students order by other_student_details desc

column1: Find the given name of the students who permanently live in the country Haiti or have the phone number 09700166582.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = "Haiti" or t2.cell_mobile_
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = 'Haiti' union select first_name from students where cell_mobile_number = '09700166582'

column1: What are the given names of the students who live in Haiti permanently or have the phone number 09700166582?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = "Haiti" or t2.cell_mobile_
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = 'Haiti' union select first_name from students where cell_mobile_number = '09700166582'

column1: find the package option of the tv channel that do not have any animation directed by Ben Jones.

column1: What are the maximum and minimum values of area codes?

column3: voter_1 | select max(area_code), min(area_code) from area_code_state

column1: What are the names of the participants whose names are not 'Jessie Alloway'
column2: select contestant_name from contestants except select t1.contestant_name from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number
column3: voter_1 | select contestant_name from contestants where contestant_name!= 'Jessie Alloway'

column1: List the area codes in which voters voted both for the participant 'Tabatha Gehling' and the participant 'Kelly Clauss'.
column2: select area_code from votes as t1 join contestants as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join votes as t3 on t1.vote_id = t3.vote_id and t2.contestant_number = t3.contestant_number
column3: voter_1 | select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'

column3: network_1 | select avg(grade) from highschooler where id in (select t1.student_id from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id)

column1: Which veterinarians live in the state of Indiana or have done more than 2 medical cares? List his or her id, family name and cell phone.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.first_name, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column2: select t2.professional_id, t2.last_name, t2.cell_number from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t2.state = 'Indiana' union select t2.professional_id, t2.last_name, t2.cell_number from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t2.state = 'Indiana'
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1

column3: pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: How many countries does each continent have? List the continent id, continent name and the number of countries.

column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
