column1: What is the number of car models that are produced by each maker and what is the id and full name of each maker?
column2: select count(*), t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname!= "id" group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select count(*), t2.fullname, t2.id from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.id;

column1: How many car makers are there in france?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers where country = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: What is the number of makers of care in France?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: How many car models are produced in the usa?
column2: select count(*) from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.continent
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What is the count of the car models produced in the United States?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.country = "United States"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What are the countries having at least one car maker? List name and id.
column2: select t1.country, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What are the names and ids of all countries with at least one car maker?
column2: select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: Which countries in europe have at least 3 car manufacturers?
column2: select t2.country from continents as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.contid = t2.country where t1.continent = 'europe' group by t2.country having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What are the names of all European countries with at least 3 manufacturers?
column2: select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t1.country having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What is the largest amount of horsepower for the models with 3 cylinders and what make is it?
column2: select max(horsepower) from cars_data where cylinders = 3 intersect select make from car_names group by make having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the car model with the highest mpg ?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: How many car models were produced by the maker with full name American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What is the number of car models created by the car maker American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What are the names and ids of all makers with more than 3 models?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = 'General Motors' or t1.we
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different models created by either the car maker General Motors or weighed more than 3500?
column2: select distinct model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = "General Motors" union select distinct model from model_list as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.weight > 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different years in which there were cars produced that weighed less than 4000 and also cars that weighted more than 3000 ?
column2: select distinct year from cars_data where weight < 4000 intersect select distinct year from cars_data where weight > 3000
column3: car_1 | select distinct year from cars_data where weight between 3000 and 4000;

column1: For a volvo model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select cylinders from cars_data where accelerate = (select min(accelerate) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'volvo' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have a larger accelerate than the car with the largest horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of cars with a greater accelerate than the one with the most horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: For all of the 4 cylinder cars, which model has the most horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select make, t1.id from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) except select t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id where t2.cylinders > 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower , what are the make ids and names of all those with less than 4 cylinders ?
column2: select t2.make, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders < 4;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
column2: select model from model_list where weight < 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor Company?
column2: select distinct model from model_list where weight < 3500 and model not in (select t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = 'Ford Motor Company')
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makers ? List the id and the maker .
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'fiat' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.maker group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid =
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce fiat model ?
column2: select t2.countryid, t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t1.maker = 3 union select t2.countryid, t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t1.maker = "Fiat" group by t2.countryid having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: How many flights have destination ATO?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: Count the number of flights into ATO.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: How many flights arriving in Aberdeen city?
column2: select count(*) from (select t1.sourceairport from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Return the number of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select count(*) from (select t1.sourceairport from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: How many 'United Airlines' flights go to Airport 'ASY'?
column2: flight_
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "United Airlines" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: How many United Airlines flights go to City 'Aberdeen'?
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where destairport = (select destairport from airports as t3 join
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: Count the number of United Airlines flights that arrive in Aberdeen.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: Which city has most number of arriving flights?
column2: select t2.city from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has the most frequent destination airport?
column2: select city from airports group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has most number of departing flights?
column2: select t2.city from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the airport code of the airport with the most flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the code of airport that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Which airline has most number of flights?
column2: select t1.airline from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What airline serves the most flights?
column2: select t1.airline from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What is the abbreviation of the airilne has the fewest flights and what country is it in?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.abbreviation = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: What are flight numbers of flights arriving at City "Aberdeen"?
column2: select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: How many flights land in Aberdeen or Abilene?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen" or t2.city = "Abilene"

column1: Find the name of airports which do not have any flight in and out.
column2: select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport, destairport from flights)
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: Which airports do not have departing or arriving flights?
column2: select airport
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: For each shop, return the number of employees working there and the name of the shop.
column2: select count(*), t3.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id join employee as t3 on t1.employee_id = t3.employee_id join shop as t4 on t2.shop_id = t4.shop_id
column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select count(*), t2.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id group by t2.name

column1: What are the different template type codes, and how many documents use each type?
column2: select template_type_code, count(*) from templates group by template_type_code
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code, count(*) from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code

column1: Return the code of the template type that is most commonly used in documents.
column2: select template_type_code from templates group by template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Return the different document ids along with the number of paragraphs corresponding to each, ordered by id.
column2: select document_id, count(*) from paragraphs group by document_id order by count(*) desc
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select document_id, count(*) from paragraphs group by document_id order by document_id

column1: Show all document ids, names and the number of paragraphs in each document.
column2: select document_id, document_name, count(*) from documents group by document_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.document_id, t2.document_name, count(*) from paragraphs as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.document_id = t2.document_id group by t1.document_id

column1: What are the ids and names of each document, as well as the number of paragraphs in each?
column2: select document_id, document_name, count(*) from documents group by document_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.document_id, t2.document_name, count(*) from paragraphs as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.document_id = t2.document_id group by t1.document_id

column1: List the name of teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' .
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= "Little Lever Urban District"
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: What are the names of the teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' ?
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= "Little Lever Urban District"
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t1.id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select t2.visitor_id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1

column1: What is the total ticket expense of the visitors whose membership level is 1?
column2: select sum(num_of_ticket) from visit as t1 join visitor as t2 on t1.visitor_id = t2.id where t2.level_of_membership = 1
column3: museum_visit | select sum(t2.total_spent) from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id where t1.level_of_membership = 1

column1: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.
column2: select count(*) from visitor where id not in ( select visitor_id from visit where open_year > 2010
column3: museum_visit | select count(*) from visitor where id not in (select t2.visitor_id from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t1.open_year > 2010)

column1: Find the highest rank of losers in all matches.
column2: select loser_rank from matches order by loser_rank desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What is the best rank of losers across all matches?
column2: select loser_rank from matches group by loser_rank order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' intersect select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = 'Australian Open'

column1: Find the first name and country code of the oldest player.

column1: What is the name of the winner who has won the most matches, and how many rank points does this player have?

column1: List the name, date and result of each battle.

column1: What is maximum and minimum death toll caused each time?
column2: select max(t1.killed), min(t1.killed) from death as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t1.id
column3: battle_death | select max(killed), min(killed) from death

column1: What is the average number of injuries caused each time?
column2: select avg(injured), t1.id from death as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t1.id
column3: battle_death | select avg(injured) from death

column1: What are the death and injury situations caused by the ship with tonnage 't'?
column2: select t1.killed, t1.injured from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.ship_
column3: battle_death | select t1.killed, t1.injured from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id where t2.tonnage = 't'

column1: What are the ids and names of the battles that led to more than 10 people killed in total.
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id = t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t2.killed) > 10
column3: battle_death | select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle join death as t3 on t2.id = t3.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t3.killed) > 10

column1: What is the ship id and name that caused most total injuries?

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) <= 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What are the names of high schoolers who both have friends and are liked?
column2: select t1.name from highschooler as t1 join friend as t2 on t1.id = t2.student_id join likes as t3 on t2.student_id = t3.student_id
column3: network_1 | select t2.name from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id intersect select t2.name from likes as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.liked_id = t2.id

column1: Show the names of high schoolers who have likes, and numbers of likes for each.
column2: select t1.name, count(*) from highschooler as t1 join likes as t2 on t1.id = t2.liked_id group by t2.liked_id
column3: network_1 | select t2.name, count(*) from likes as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id group by t1.student_id

column1: What are the names of high schoolers who have likes, and how many likes does each have?
column2: select t1.name, count(*) from highschooler as t1 join likes as t2 on t1.id = t2.liked_id group by t2.liked_id
column3: network_1 | select t2.name, count(*) from likes as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id group by t1.student_id

column1: What is the name of the high schooler who has the greatest number of likes?
column2: select t1.name from highschooler as t1 join likes as t2 on t1.id = t2.liked_id group by t2.liked_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: network_1 | select t2.name from likes as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Show the names of students who have a grade higher than 5 and have at least 2 friends.
column2: select name from highschooler where grade > 5 intersect select t1.name from highschooler as t1 join friend as t2 on t1.id = t2.friend_id group by t2.friend_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: network_1 | select t2.name from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id where t2.grade > 5 group by t1.student_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: What are the names of high schoolers who have a grade of over 5 and have 2 or more friends?
column2: select name from highschooler where grade > 5 intersect select t1.name from highschooler as t1 join friend as t2 on t1.id = t2.friend_id group by t2.friend_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: network_1 | select t2.name from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id where t2.grade > 5 group by t1.student_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: What is the average grade of students who have friends?
column2: select avg(t1.grade) from highschooler as t1 join friend as t2 on t1.id = t2.friend_id
column3: network_1 | select avg(grade) from highschooler where id in (select t1.student_id from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id)

column1: What is the lowest grade of students who do not have any friends?
column2: select grade from highschooler where id not in (select student_id from friend)
column3: network_1 | select min(grade) from highschooler where id not in (select t1.student_id from friend as t1 join highschooler as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.id)

column1: Find the average age of the dogs who went through treatments.
column2: select avg(age) from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id
column3: dog_kennels | select avg(age) from dogs where dog_id in ( select dog_id from treatments )

column1: Which professionals live in the state of Indiana or have done treatment on more than 2 treatments? List his or her id, last name and cell phone.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having t1.state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column1: Find the id, last name and cell phone of the professionals who live in the state of Indiana or have performed more than two treatments.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having t1.state = "Indiana" union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column1: Which dogs have not cost their owner more than 1000 for treatment ? List the dog names .
column2: select name from dogs except select t2.name from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.cost_of_treatment > 1000
column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: What are the names of the dogs for which the owner has not spend more than 1000 for treatment ?
column2: select name from dogs where dog_id not in (select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having cost_of_treatment > 1000)
column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: Which first names are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names?
column2: select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select t2.first_name from dogs as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.professional_id
column3: dog_kennels | select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select name from dogs

column1: Find the first names that are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names.
column2: select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select t2.first_name from dogs as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.professional_id
column3: dog_kennels | select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select name from dogs

column1: Tell me the owner id and last name of the owner who spent the most on treatments of his or her dogs.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t3.dog_id = t2.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which owner has paid the largest amount of money in total for their dogs? Show the owner id and zip code.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t2.charge_amount
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1

column1: Find the owner id and zip code of the owner who spent the most money in total for his or her dogs.
column2: select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t2.cost_of_treatment
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.zip_code from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by sum(t3.cost_of_treatment) desc limit 1

column1: What are the first name and last name of the professionals who have done treatment with cost below average?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments)
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )

column1: Which professionals have operated a treatment that costs less than the average? Give me theor first names and last names.
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments)
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )

column1: List the names of the dogs of the rarest breed and the treatment dates of them.
column2: select t2.name, t1.date_of_treatment from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t2.breed_code = (select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) desc limit 1)
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.name, t2.date_of_treatment from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.breed_code = ( select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) asc limit 1 )

column1: Which dogs are of the rarest breed? Show their names and treatment dates.
column2: select name, date_of_treatment from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t2.breed_code = (select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) desc limit 1)
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.name, t2.date_of_treatment from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.breed_code = ( select breed_code from dogs group by breed_code order by count(*) asc limit 1 )

column1: Which dogs are owned by someone who lives in Virginia? List the owner's first name and the dog's name.
column2: select first_name, last_name from owners where state = 'Virginia'
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: Find the first names of owners living in Virginia and the names of dogs they own.
column2: select first_name, last_name from owners where state = 'Virginia'
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: List the last name of the owner owning the youngest dog.
column2: select t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id order by t1.age asc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: Who owns the youngest dog? Give me his or her last name.
column2: select t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id order by t1.age asc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: Which professionals live in a city containing the substring 'West'? List his or her role, street, city and state.
column2: select first_name, last_name, street, city, state from professionals where city like "%west%"
column3: dog_kennels | select role_code, street, city, state from professionals where city like '%west%'

column1: How much does the most recent treatment cost?
column2: select max(cost_of_treatment) from treatments
column3: dog_kennels | select cost_of_treatment from treatments order by date_of_treatment desc limit 1

column1: How much does the most expensive charge type costs?
column2: select charge_type, max(charge_amount) from charges group by charge_type
column3: dog_kennels | select max(charge_amount) from charges

column1: What are all the possible breed type and size type combinations?
column2: select count(distinct breed_code), count(distinct size_code) from dogs
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct breed_code, size_code from dogs

column1: Show the property type descriptions of properties belonging to that code.
column2: select t1.property_type_description from ref_property_types as t1 join properties as t2 on t1.property_type_code = t2.property_type_code
column3: real_estate_properties | select t2.property_type_description from properties as t1 join ref_property_types as t2 on t1.property_type_code = t2.property_type_code group by t1.property_type_code

column1: What are the names of properties that are either houses or apartments with more than 1 room?
column2: select property_name from properties where property_type_code = "House" or room_count > 1
column3: real_estate_properties | select property_name from properties where property_type_code = "House" union select property_name from properties where property_type_code = "Apartment" and room_count > 1

column1: What is the average, minimum, and maximum age for all French singers?
column2: select avg(age), min(age), max(age) from singer where country = 'F'
column3: concert_singer | select avg(age), min(age), max(age) from singer where country = 'France'

column1: What is the maximum capacity and the average of all stadiums ?
column2: select max(capacity), avg(capacity) from stadium
column3: concert_singer | select max(capacity), average from stadium

column1: What are the names , themes , and number of singers for every concert ?
column2: select concert_name, theme, count(*) from concert group by concert_id
column3: concert_singer | select t2.concert_name, t2.theme, count(*) from singer_in_concert as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.concert_id = t2.concert_id group by t2.concert_id

column1: What are the number of concerts that occurred in the stadium with the largest capacity ?
column2: select count(*) from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id order by t2.capacity desc limit 1
column3: concert_singer | select count(*) from concert where stadium_id = (select stadium_id from stadium order by capacity desc limit 1)

column1: Find the major and age of students who do not have a cat pet.
column2: select major, age from student except select t1.major, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'
column3: pets_1 | select major, age from student where stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: Find the first name and age of students who have a dog but do not have a cat as a pet.
column2: select fname, age from student where stuid in (select t1.stuid from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid where t2.pettype = 'dog' except select t1.stuid from has_pet as t1 join pets as t2 on t1.petid = t2.petid where t2.pettype = 'cat')
column3: pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: What is the first name of every student who has a dog but does not have a cat?
column2: select t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' except select t1.fname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t2.petid = t3.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat'
column3: pets_1 | select t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'dog' and t1.stuid not in (select t1.stuid from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pettype = 'cat')

column1: Find the first name and age of students who have a pet.
column2: select fname, age from student where stuid in (select stuid from has_pet)
column3: pets_1 | select distinct t1.fname, t1.age from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid

column1: Find the last name of the student who has a cat that is age 3.
column2: select t2.lname from pets as t1 join student as t2 on t1.petid = t2.stuid where t1.pet_age = 3 and t2.fname = "M"
column3: pets_1 | select t1.lname from student as t1 join has_pet as t2 on t1.stuid = t2.stuid join pets as t3 on t3.petid = t2.petid where t3.pet_age = 3 and t3.pettype = 'cat'

column1: How many countries does each continent have? List the continent id, continent name and the number of countries.
column2: select t1.continent, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.continent = t2.continent group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: For each continent, list its id, name, and how many countries it has?
column2: select continent, countryname, count(*) from countries group by continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.contid, t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent group by t1.contid;

column1: How many models does each car maker produce? List maker full name, id and the number.
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: What is the full name of each car maker, along with its id and how many models it produces?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id, count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id;

column1: Which model of the car has the minimum horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: What is the model of the car with the smallest amount of horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.horsepower asc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.horsepower asc limit 1;

column1: Find the model of the car whose weight is below the average weight.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: What is the model for the car with a weight smaller than the average?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.weight < (select avg(weight) from cars_data)

column1: Find the name of the makers that produced some cars in the year of 1970?
column2: select t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid join cars_data as t3 on t3.id = t2.makeid where t3.year = 1970
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model join cars_data as t4 on t3.makeid = t4.id where t4.year = '1970';

column1: What is the name of the different car makers who produced a car in 1970?
column2: select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.year = 1970
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model join cars_data as t4 on t3.makeid = t4.id where t4.year = '1970';

column1: Find the make and production time of the cars that were produced in the earliest year?
column2: select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid order by t1.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: What is the maker of the carr produced in the earliest year and what year was it?
column2: select t1.maker, t2.year from car_makers as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id order by t2.year limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t2.make, t1.year from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.year = (select min(year) from cars_data);

column1: Which distinct car models are the produced after 1980?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.year > 1980
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year > 1980;

column1: What are the different models for the cards produced after 1980?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.year > 1980
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id where t3.year > 1980;

column1: How many car makers are there in each continents? List the continent name and the count.
column2: select t2.continent, count(*) from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: What is the name of each continent and how many car makers are there in each one?
column2: select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.contid = t2.country group by t1.continent
column3: car_1 | select t1.continent, count(*) from continents as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.contid = t2.continent join car_makers as t3 on t2.countryid = t3.country group by t1.continent;

column1: What is the number of car models that are produced by each maker and what is the id and full name of each maker?
column2: select count(*), t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname!= "id" group by t1.maker
column3: car_1 | select count(*), t2.fullname, t2.id from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.id;

column1: How many car makers are there in france?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers where country = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: What is the number of makers of care in France?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = "France"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t2.countryname = 'france';

column1: How many car models are produced in the usa?
column2: select count(*) from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.continent
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What is the count of the car models produced in the United States?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.country = "United States"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id join countries as t3 on t2.country = t3.countryid where t3.countryname = 'usa';

column1: What are the countries having at least one car maker? List name and id.
column2: select t1.country, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What are the names and ids of all countries with at least one car maker?
column2: select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: Which countries in europe have at least 3 car manufacturers?
column2: select t2.country from continents as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.contid = t2.country where t1.continent = 'europe' group by t2.country having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What are the names of all European countries with at least 3 manufacturers?
column2: select t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid group by t1.country having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What is the largest amount of horsepower for the models with 3 cylinders and what make is it?
column2: select max(horsepower) from cars_data where cylinders = 3 intersect select make from car_names group by make having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the car model with the highest mpg ?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: How many car models were produced by the maker with full name American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What is the number of car models created by the car maker American Motor Company?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = "American motor Company"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What are the names and ids of all makers with more than 3 models?
column2: select t1.fullname, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = 'General Motors' or t1.we
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different models created by either the car maker General Motors or weighed more than 3500?
column2: select distinct model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = "General Motors" union select distinct model from model_list as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.weight > 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different years in which there were cars produced that weighed less than 4000 and also cars that weighted more than 3000 ?
column2: select distinct year from cars_data where weight < 4000 intersect select distinct year from cars_data where weight > 3000
column3: car_1 | select distinct year from cars_data where weight between 3000 and 4000;

column1: For a volvo model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select cylinders from cars_data where accelerate = (select min(accelerate) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'volvo' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have a larger accelerate than the car with the largest horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of cars with a greater accelerate than the one with the most horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: For all of the 4 cylinder cars, which model has the most horsepower?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t1.cylinders = 4 order by t1.horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select make, t1.id from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) except select t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id where t2.cylinders > 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower , what are the make ids and names of all those with less than 4 cylinders ?
column2: select t2.make, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders < 4;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
column2: select model from model_list where weight < 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor Company?
column2: select distinct model from model_list where weight < 3500 and model not in (select t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = 'Ford Motor Company')
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makers ? List the id and the maker .
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'fiat' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.maker group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid =
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce fiat model ?
column2: select t2.countryid, t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t1.maker = 3 union select t2.countryid, t2.countryname from car_makers as t1 join countries as t2 on t1.country = t2.countryid where t1.maker = "Fiat" group by t2.countryid having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: How many flights have destination ATO?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: Count the number of flights into ATO.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: How many flights arriving in Aberdeen city?
column2: select count(*) from (select t1.sourceairport from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Return the number of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select count(*) from (select t1.sourceairport from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: How many 'United Airlines' flights go to Airport 'ASY'?
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline join airports as t3 on t2.sourceairport = t3.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "United Airlines" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: How many United Airlines flights go to City 'Aberdeen'?
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where destairport = (select destairport from airports as t3 join
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: Count the number of United Airlines flights that arrive in Aberdeen.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: Which city has most number of arriving flights?
column2: select t2.city from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has the most frequent destination airport?
column2: select city from airports group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has most number of departing flights?
column2: select t2.city from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the airport code of the airport with the most flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the code of airport that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Which airline has most number of flights?
column2: select t1.airline from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What airline serves the most flights?
column2: select t1.airline from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What is the abbreviation of the airilne has the fewest flights and what country is it in?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.abbreviation = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: What are flight numbers of flights arriving at City "Aberdeen"?
column2: select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: How many flights land in Aberdeen or Abilene?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen" or t2.city = "Abilene"

column1: Find the name of airports which do not have any flight in and out.
column2: select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport, destairport from flights)
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: Which airports do not have departing or arriving flights?
column2: select airport
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: For each shop, return the number of employees working there and the name of the shop.
column2: select count(*), t3.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id join employee as t3 on t1.employee_id = t3.employee_id join shop as t4 on t2.shop_id = t4.shop_id
column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select count(*), t2.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id group by t2.name

column1: What are the different template type codes, and how many documents use each type?
column2: select template_type_code, count(*) from templates group by template_type_code
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code, count(*) from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code

column1: Return the code of the template type that is most commonly used in documents.
column2: select template_type_code from templates group by template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Return the different document ids along with the number of paragraphs corresponding to each, ordered by id.
column2: select document_id, count(*) from paragraphs group by document_id order by count(*) desc
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select document_id, count(*) from paragraphs group by document_id order by document_id

column1: Show all document ids, names and the number of paragraphs in each document.
column2: select document_id, document_name, count(*) from documents group by document_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.document_id, t2.document_name, count(*) from paragraphs as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.document_id = t2.document_id group by t1.document_id

column1: What are the ids and names of each document, as well as the number of paragraphs in each?
column2: select document_id, document_name, count(*) from documents group by document_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.document_id, t2.document_name, count(*) from paragraphs as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.document_id = t2.document_id group by t1.document_id

column1: List the name of teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' .
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= "Little Lever Urban District"
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: What are the names of the teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' ?
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= "Little Lever Urban District"
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t1.id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select t2.visitor_id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1

column1: What is the total ticket expense of the visitors whose membership level is 1?
column2: select sum(num_of_ticket) from visit as t1 join visitor as t2 on t1.visitor_id = t2.id where t2.level_of_membership = 1
column3: museum_visit | select sum(t2.total_spent) from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id where t1.level_of_membership = 1

column1: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.
column2: select count(*) from visitor where id not in ( select visitor_id from visit where open_year > 2010
column3: museum_visit | select count(*) from visitor where id not in (select t2.visitor_id from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t1.open_year > 2010)

column1: Find the highest rank of losers in all matches.
column2: select loser_rank from matches order by loser_rank desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What is the best rank of losers across all matches?
column2: select loser_rank from matches group by loser_rank order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What are the names of tournaments that have more than 10 matches?
column2: select tourney_name from matches group by tourney_id having count(*) > 10
column3: wta_1 | select tourney_name from matches group by tourney_name having count(*) > 10

column1: What are the country code and first name of the players who won in both tourney WTA Championships and Australian Open?
column2: select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = "WTA Championships" intersect select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id join matches as t3 on t2.tourney_id = t3.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = "Australian Open"
column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' intersect select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id where t2.tourney_name = 'Australian Open'

column1: Find the first name and country code of the oldest player.
column2: select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: What is the first name and country code of the oldest player?
column2: select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: Find the first name and country code of the player who did the most number of tours.

column3: world_1 | select t1.continent from country as t1 join countrylanguage as t2 on t1.code = t2.countrycode group by t1.continent order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which continent speaks the most languages?

column1: How many countries speak both English and Dutch?
