column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What is the maximum horsepower and the make of the car models with 3 cylinders?
column2: select max(horsepower), t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: What is the largest amount of horsepower for the models with 3 cylinders and what make is it?
column2: select max(horsepower), t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid order by t1.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model_list group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t2.model from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different models created by either the car maker General Motors or weighed more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.modelid join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id where t3.fullname = "General Motors" or t1.
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: In which years cars were produced weighing no less than 3000 and no more than 4000 ?
column2: select year from cars_data where weight <= 3000 and weight > 4000
column3: car_1 | select distinct year from cars_data where weight between 3000 and 4000;

column1: What are the different years in which there were cars produced that weighed less than 4000 and also cars that weighted more than 3000 ?
column2: select distinct year from cars_data where weight < 4000 intersect select distinct year from cars_data where weight > 3000
column3: car_1 | select distinct year from cars_data where weight between 3000 and 4000;

column1: For a volvo model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t2.model = "volvo" order by t1.accelerate limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'volvo' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have a larger accelerate than the car with the largest horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of cars with a greater accelerate than the one with the most horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
column2: select model from car_names join cars_data on cars_data.id = cars_data.id where cylinders = 4 order by horsepower desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select t1.makeid, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id where t2.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) intersect select t1.make, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.make = t2.id group by t1.makeid having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower , what are the make ids and names of all those with less than 4 cylinders ?
column2: select distinct t1.make, t1.
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders < 4;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
column2: select t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor Company?
column2: select distinct t2.model from cars_data as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makers ? List the id and the maker .
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid group by t1.maker having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'fiat' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id where t2.maker = "fiat" group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce fiat model ?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.maker where t2.model = 'fiat'
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: Count the number of United Airlines flights arriving in ASY Airport.
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "United Airlines" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: Which city has the most frequent destination airport?
column2: select city from airports group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the code of airport that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Give the code of the airport with the least flights.
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Which airline has most number of flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What is the abbreviation of the airilne has the fewest flights and what country is it in?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.uid order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Find the name of airports which do not have any flight in and out.
column2: select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport, destairport from flights)
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: What are the ids of templates with template type code PP or PPT?
column2: select template_id from templates where template_type_code = "PP" or template_type_code = "PP"
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select template_id from templates where template_type_code = "PP" or template_type_code = "PPT"

column1: Return the ids of templates that have the code PP or PPT.
column2: select template_id from templates where template_type_code = "PP" or template_type_code = "PP"
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select template_id from templates where template_type_code = "PP" or template_type_code = "PPT"

column1: Show all template type codes and the number of documents using each type.
column2: select template_type_code, count(*) from templates group by template_type_code
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code, count(*) from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code

column1: What are the different template type codes, and how many documents use each type?
column2: select template_type_code, count(*) from templates group by template_type_code
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code, count(*) from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code

column1: Return the code of the template type that is most commonly used in documents.
column2: select template_type_code from templates group by template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select t1.template_type_code from templates as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_id = t2.template_id group by t1.template_type_code order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach.
column2: select t2.name, t1.course_id from course_arrange as t1 join teacher as t2 on t1.teacher_id = t2.teacher_id
column3: course_teach | select t3.name, t2.course from course_arrange as t1 join course as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id join teacher as t3 on t1.teacher_id = t3.teacher_id

column1: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id order by total_spent desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select t2.visitor_id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1

column1: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.
column2: select count(*) from visitor where id not in ( select visitor_id from visit where open_year > 2010
column3: museum_visit | select count(*) from visitor where id not in (select t2.visitor_id from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t1.open_year > 2010)

column1: Find the highest rank of losers in all matches.
column2: select max(loser_rank) from matches
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What is the best rank of losers across all matches?
column2: select loser_rank from matches group by loser_rank order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: Find the first name and country code of the oldest player.
column2: select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: What is the first name and country code of the oldest player?
column2: select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: What are the full names of all left handed players, in order of birth date?
column2: select first_name, last_name from players where hand = "left" order by birth_date
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, last_name from players where hand = 'L' order by birth_date

column1: Find the first name and country code of the player who did the most number of tours.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.country_code from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id order by t2.tours desc limit 1

column1: What is the first name and country code of the player with the most tours?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.country_code from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id order by t2.tours desc limit 1

column1: What is the name of the winner who has won the most matches, and how many rank points does this player have?
column2: select winner_name, winner_rank_points from matches as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.winner_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select winner_name, winner_rank_points from matches group by winner_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the name of the winner who has the highest rank points and participated in the Australian Open tourney.
column2: select t1.winner_name from matches as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.loser_id = t2.player_id where t1.tourney_name = "Australian open" order by t2.winner_rank_points
column3: wta_1 | select winner_name from matches where tourney_name = 'Australian Open' order by winner_rank_points desc limit 1

column1: What is the name of the winner with the most rank points who participated in the Australian Open tournament?
column2: select t1.winner_name from matches as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.loser_id = t2.player_id where t1.tourney_name = "Australian open" order by t2.winner_rank_points
column3: wta_1 | select winner_name from matches where tourney_name = 'Australian Open' order by winner_rank_points desc limit 1

column1: What are the first names of all players, and their total ranking points?
column2: select t1.first_name, sum(t2.ranking_points) from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.player_id
column3: wta_1 | select sum(ranking_points), t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.first_name

column1: How many different winners both participated in the WTA Championships and were left handed?
column2: select count(*) from matches as t1 join players as t2 on t1.loser_id = t2.player_id where t1.tourney_name = "WTA Championships" and t2.hand = "left"
column3: wta_1 | select count(distinct winner_name) from matches where tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' and winner_hand = 'L'

column1: Find the number of left handed winners who participated in the WTA Championships.
column2: select count(*) from matches where tourney_name = "WTA Championships" and winner_hand = "left"
column3: wta_1 | select count(distinct winner_name) from matches where tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' and winner_hand = 'L'

column1: List the name, date and result of each battle.
column2: select name, date, result from battle
column3: battle_death | select name, date from battle

column1: What is maximum and minimum death toll caused each time?
column2: select max(killed), min(killed) from death group by caused_by_ship_id
column3: battle_death | select max(killed), min(killed) from death

column1: What is the average number of injuries caused each time?
column2: select avg(injured) from death group by injured
column3: battle_death | select avg(injured) from death

column1: What are the death and injury situations caused by the ship with tonnage 't'?
column2: select caused_by_ship_id, t1.killed from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = caused_by_ship_id where t2.tonnage = 't'
column3: battle_death | select t1.killed, t1.injured from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id where t2.tonnage = 't'

column1: What are the ids and names of the battles that led to more than 10 people killed in total.
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id = t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t2.killed) > 10
column3: battle_death | select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle join death as t3 on t2.id = t3.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t3.killed) > 10

column1: What is the ship id and name that caused most total injuries?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from ship as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id = t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id order by sum(t2.injured) desc limit 1
column3: battle_death | select t2.id, t2.name from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t2.id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: what are all the addresses including line 1 and line 2?
column2: select address_id, line_1 + line_2 from addresses union select address_id, line_3 from addresses
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select line_1, line_2 from addresses

column1: What is the first and second line for all addresses?
column2: select t1.line_1, t1.line_2 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.permanent_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select line_1, line_2 from addresses

column1: How many different departments offer degrees?
column2: select count(distinct t2.department_name) from degree_programs as t1 join departments as t2 on t1.department_id = t2.department_id group by t2.department_name
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(distinct department_id) from degree_programs

column1: What are the names and ids of every course with less than 2 sections?
column2: select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) < 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) <= 2

column1: Who are enrolled in 2 degree programs in one semester? List the first name, middle name and last name and the id.
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.middle_name, t2.last_name, t1.student_enrolment_id from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t1.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column1: What are the first, middle, and last names, along with the ids, of all students who enrolled in 2 degree programs in one semester?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) >= 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column1: Who is enrolled in a Bachelor degree program? List the first name, middle name, last name.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = "Bache"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What are the first, middle, and last names for everybody enrolled in a Bachelors program?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.middle_name, t2.last_name from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id where t1.degree_program_id = "Bachelor"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: Find the kind of program which most number of students are enrolled in?
column2: select degree_program_id from student_enrolment group by degree_program_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.degree_summary_name from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id group by t1.degree_summary_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which student has enrolled for the most times in any program? List the id, first name, middle name, last name, the number of enrollments and student id.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.student_id, t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the first, middle, and last name, along with the id and number of enrollments, for the student who enrolled the most in any program?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id, count(*) from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.student_id, t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the name of the course with the most students enrolled?
column2: select t1.course_name from courses as t1 join student_enrolment_courses as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name from courses as t1 join student_enrolment_courses as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the last name of the students who currently live in the state of North Carolina but have not registered in any degree program.
column2: select last_name from students where current_address_id like '%nc%'
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.current_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.state_province_county = 'NorthCarolina' except select distinct t3.last_name from students as t3 join student_enrolment as t4 on t3.student_id = t4.student_id

column1: What are the last name of the students who live in North Carolina but have not registered in any degree programs?
column2: select last_name from students where current_address_id like '%nc%'
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.current_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.state_province_county = 'NorthCarolina' except select distinct t3.last_name from students as t3 join student_enrolment as t4 on t3.student_id = t4.student_id

column1: What is the mobile phone number of the student named Timmothy Ward ?
column2: select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name = "Timmothy" and last_name = "Ward"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name = 'timmothy' and last_name = 'ward'

column1: Who is the first student to register? List the first name, middle name and last name.
column2: select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered asc limit 1

column1: What is the first, middle, and last name of the first student to register?
column2: select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name, middle_name, last_name from students order by date_first_registered asc limit 1

column1: Whose permanent address is different from his or her current address? List his or her first name.
column2: select t2.first_name from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.permanent_address_id where t1.state_province_county!= "No"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: What is the first name of the student whose permanent address is different from his or her current one?
column2: select first_name from students where permanent_address_id!= "null"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: Which address holds the most number of students currently? List the address id and all lines.
column2: select t1.address_id, t1.line_1 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.address_id, t1.line_1, t1.line_2 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the earliest date of a transcript release, and what details can you tell me?
column2: select transcript_date, other_details from transcripts
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select transcript_date, other_details from transcripts order by transcript_date asc limit 1

column1: How many times at most can a course enrollment result show in different transcripts? Also show the course enrollment id.
column2: select count(distinct student_enrolment_id), t1.student_enrolment_id from student_enrolment_courses as t1 join transcript_contents as t2 on t1.student_course_id = t2.student_course_id group by t1.student_enrolment_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the maximum number of times that a course shows up in different transcripts and what is that course's enrollment id?
column2: select max(course_id), student_enrolment_id from student_enrolment_courses
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Show the date of the transcript which shows the least number of results, also list the id.
column2: select transcript_date, transcript_id from transcripts group by transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1

column1: What is the date and id of the transcript with the least number of results?
column2: select transcript_date, transcript_id from transcripts group by transcript_id order by count(*) limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1

column1: Find the semester when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.
column2: select t2.semester_name from student_enrolment as t1 join semesters as t2 on t1.semester_id = t2.semester_id join degree_programs as t3 on t1.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select t2.se
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What is the id of the semester that had both Masters and Bachelors students enrolled?
column2: select semester_id from student_enrolment where degree_program_id = "MA" intersect select semester_id from student_enrolment where degree_program_id = "BA"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What are the different addresses that have students living there?
column2: select distinct t1.address_id from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.permanent_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(distinct current_address_id) from students

column1: List all the student details in reversed lexicographical order.
column2: select other_student_details from students order by other_student_details
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select other_student_details from students order by other_student_details desc

column1: Find the first name of the students who permanently live in the country Haiti or have the cell phone number 09700166582 .
column2: select t2.first_name from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.permanent_address_id where t1.country = "Haiti" or t2.cell_mobile_number = "09700166582"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = 'haiti' or t1.cell_mobile_number = '09700166582'

column1: Find the series name and country of the tv channel that is playing some cartoons directed by Ben Jones and Michael Chang?
column2: select t2.series_name, t2.country from cartoon as t1 join tv_channel as t2 on t1.channel = t2.id where t1.directed_by = 'Ben Jones' intersect select t2.series_name, t2.country from cartoon as t1 join tv_channel as t2 on t1.channel = t2.id where t1.directed_by = 'Michain'
column3: tvshow | select t1.series_name, t1.country from tv_channel as t1 join cartoon as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t2.directed_by = 'Michael Chang' intersect select t1.series_name, t1.country from tv_channel as t1 join cartoon as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t2.directed_by = 'Ben Jones'

column1: find id of the tv channels that from the countries where have more than two tv channels.
column2: select id from tv_channel where country > 2
column3: tvshow | select id from tv_channel group by country having count(*) > 2

column1: What are the ids of all tv channels that have more than 2 TV channels?

column2: select id from tv_channel except select id from cartoon where directed_by = "Ben Jones"
column3: tvshow | select id from tv_channel except select channel from cartoon where directed_by = 'Ben Jones'

column3: tvshow | select package_option from tv_channel where id not in (select channel from cartoon where directed_by = 'Ben Jones')

column1: List the area codes in which voters voted both for the contestant 'Tabatha Gehling' and the contestant 'Kelly Clauss'.
column2: select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.state = t2.state join contestants as t3 on t2.contestant_number = t3.contestant_number where t3.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.state = t2.area_code
column3: voter_1 | select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select t1.make, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower , what are the make ids and names of all those with less than 4 cylinders ?
column2: select t1.make, t2.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t3 on t1.makeid = t3.id
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders < 4;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
column2: select t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.modelid join car_makers as t3 on
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor Company?
column2: select distinct model from car_names where weight < 3500 and maker!= 'Ford Motor Company'
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makers ? List the id and the maker .
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'fiat' model?
column2: select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id where t2.maker = 'fiat' group by t1.countryname having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce fiat model ?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id where t2.maker = 'fiat' group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryname, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'fiat';

column1: Which country does Airline "JetBlue Airways" belong to?
column2: select country from airlines where abbreviation = "JetBlue Airways"
column3: flight_2 | select country from airlines where airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: What country is Jetblue Airways affiliated with?
column2: select country from airlines where abbreviation = "JetBlue Airways"
column3: flight_2 | select country from airlines where airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Count the number of flights into ATO.
column2: select count(*) from airports where airportcode = "ATO"
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: How many flights does airline 'JetBlue Airways' have?
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t1.abbreviation = 'JetBlue Airways'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Give the number of Jetblue Airways flights.
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.flightno where t1.abbreviation = "JetBlue Airways"
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: How many 'United Airlines' flights go to Airport 'ASY'?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "United Airlines" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: Which city is the most frequent source airport?
column2: select city from airports group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t2.airline order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What is the abbreviation of the airilne has the fewest flights and what country is it in?
column2: select t2.abbreviation, t1.country from airports as t1 join flights on t1.countryabbrev = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select distinct t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Which airports do not have departing or arriving flights?
column2: select airportname from airports except select t1.airportname from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: What are the distinct template type descriptions for the templates ever used by any document?
column2: select distinct template_type_description from ref_template_types join documents on documents.template_id = documents.template_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select distinct t1.template_type_description from ref_template_types as t1 join templates as t2 on t1.template_type_code = t2.template_type_code join documents as t3 on t2.template_id = t3.template_id

column1: Return the different descriptions for templates that have been used in a document.
column2: select distinct t1.template_type_description from ref_template_types as t1 join documents as t2 on t1.template_type_code = t2.template_id
column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select distinct t1.template_type_description from ref_template_types as t1 join templates as t2 on t1.template_type_code = t2.template_type_code join documents as t3 on t2.template_id = t3.template_id

column1: List the name of teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' .
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= 'Little Lever Urban District'
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: What are the names of the teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' ?
column2: select name from teacher where hometown!= 'Little Lever Urban District'
column3: course_teach | select name from teacher where hometown!= "little lever urban district"

column1: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach.
column2: select t1.name, t2.course_id from teacher as t1 join course_arrange as t2 on t1.teacher_id = t2.teacher_id
column3: course_teach | select t3.name, t2.course from course_arrange as t1 join course as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id join teacher as t3 on t1.teacher_id = t3.teacher_id

column1: What are the names of the people who teach math courses?
column2: select distinct t1.name from teacher as t1 join course as t2 on t1.teacher_id =
column3: course_teach | select t3.name from course_arrange as t1 join course as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id join teacher as t3 on t1.teacher_id = t3.teacher_id where t2.course = "Math"

column1: What is the average age of the visitors whose membership level is not higher than 4?
column2: select avg(age), name from visitor where level_of_membership < 4
column3: museum_visit | select avg(age) from visitor where level_of_membership <= 4

column1: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select t2.visitor_id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1

column1: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.
column2: select count(*) from visit as t1 join museum as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t2.open_year > 2010
column3: museum_visit | select count(*) from visitor where id not in (select t2.visitor_id from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t1.open_year > 2010)

column1: Find the highest rank of losers in all matches.
column2: select max(loser_rank) from matches
column3: wta_1 | select min(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What is the best rank of losers across all matches?

column1: Find the first name and country code of the oldest player.

column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: What is the first name and country code of the oldest player?
column2: select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select first_name, country_code from players order by birth_date limit 1

column1: List the first and last name of all players who are left / L hand in the order of birth date.

column3: wta_1 | select first_name, last_name from players where hand = 'L' order by birth_date

column1: What are the full names of all left handed players, in order of birth date?

column3: wta_1 | select first_name, last_name from players where hand = 'L' order by birth_date

column1: Find the first name and country code of the player who did the most number of tours.

column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id order by t2.tours desc limit 1

column1: What is the first name and country code of the player with the most tours?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.country_code from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.country_code, t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id order by t2.tours desc limit 1

column1: Find the name and rank points of the winner who won the most times.
column2: select t2.winner_name, t2.winner_rank_points from rankings as t1 join
column3: wta_1 | select winner_name, winner_rank_points from matches group by winner_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the name of the winner who has won the most matches, and how many rank points does this player have?

column3: wta_1 | select winner_name, winner_rank_points from matches group by winner_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What are the names of the winner and loser who played in the longest match?
column2: select t2.winner_name, t2.loser_name from matches as t1 join players as t2
column3: wta_1 | select winner_name, loser_name from matches order by minutes desc limit 1

column1: Find the average ranking for each player and their first name.

column3: wta_1 | select avg(ranking), t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.first_name

column1: Find the total ranking points for each player and their first name.
column2: select sum(ranking_points), t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.player_id
column3: wta_1 | select sum(ranking_points), t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.first_name

column1: What are the first names of all players, and their total ranking points?
column2: select t1.first_name, sum(t2.ranking_points) from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.player_id
column3: wta_1 | select sum(ranking_points), t1.first_name from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.first_name

column1: Find the total number of tours for each ranking date.
column2: select ranking_date, count(*) from rankings group by ranking_date
column3: wta_1 | select sum(tours), ranking_date from rankings group by ranking_date

column1: How many total tours were there for each ranking date?
column2: select ranking_date, count(*) from rankings group by ranking_date
column3: wta_1 | select sum(tours), ranking_date from rankings group by ranking_date

column1: How many different winners both participated in the WTA Championships and were left handed?
column2: select count(distinct winner_hand) from matches where tourney_name = 'WTA Championships'
column3: wta_1 | select count(distinct winner_name) from matches where tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' and winner_hand = 'L'

column1: Find the number of left handed winners who participated in the WTA Championships.
column2: select count(*) from matches where tourney_name = "WTA Championships" and winner_hand = "left"
column3: wta_1 | select count(distinct winner_name) from matches where tourney_name = 'WTA Championships' and winner_hand = 'L'

column1: What is the first name, country code, and birth date of the player with the most winner rank points across all matches?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.country_code, t1.birth_date from players as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.first_name, t1.country_code, t1.birth_date from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id order by t2.winner_rank_points desc limit 1

column1: List the name, date and result of each battle.
column2: select name, date, result from battle
column3: battle_death | select name, date from battle

column1: What is maximum and minimum death toll caused each time?
column2: select max(t1.killed), min(t1.killed) from death as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t1.id
column3: battle_death | select max(killed), min(killed) from death

column1: What is the average number of injuries caused each time?
column2: select avg(injured), t1.id from death as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t1.id
column3: battle_death | select avg(injured) from death

column1: What are the death and injury situations caused by the ship with tonnage 't'?
column2: select killed, injured from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = 'caused_by_ship_id' where t2.tonnage = 't'
column3: battle_death | select t1.killed, t1.injured from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id where t2.tonnage = 't'

column1: What are the ids and names of the battles that led to more than 10 people killed in total.
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id = t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t2.killed) > 10
column3: battle_death | select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle join death as t3 on t2.id = t3.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t3.killed) > 10

column1: What is the ship id and name that caused most total injuries?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from ship as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id = t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id order by sum(injured) desc limit 1
column3: battle_death | select t2.id, t2.name from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t2.id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: what are all the addresses including line 1 and line 2?
column2: select address_id from addresses where line_1 like "%2%"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select line_1, line_2 from addresses

column1: What is the first and second line for all addresses?
column2: select t1.line_1, t1.line_2 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select line_1, line_2 from addresses

column1: What are the names and id of courses having at most 2 sections?
column2: select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) < 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) <= 2

column1: What are the names and ids of every course with less than 2 sections?
column2: select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) < 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) <= 2

column1: Who are enrolled in 2 degree programs in one semester? List the first name, middle name and last name and the id.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id where t2.degree_program_id = 2
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column1: What are the first, middle, and last names for everybody enrolled in a Bachelors program?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.middle_name, t2.last_name from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id where t1.degree_program_id = 'Bachelor'
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: Find the kind of program which most number of students are enrolled in?
column2: select degree_program_id from student_enrolment group by degree_program_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.degree_summary_name from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id group by t1.degree_summary_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which student has enrolled for the most times in any program? List the id, first name, middle name, last name, the number of enrollments and student id.
column2: select t1.student_id, t2.first_name, t2.middle_name, count(*), t1.student_id from student_enrolment as t1 join students as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.student_id, t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the first, middle, and last name, along with the id and number of enrollments, for the student who enrolled the most in any program?
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.student_id, t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, count(*), t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What's the name of the course with most number of enrollments?
column2: select t1.course_name from courses as t1 join student_enrolment_courses as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name from courses as t1 join student_enrolment_courses as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the last name of the students who currently live in the state of North Carolina but have not registered in any degree program.
column2: select last_name from students where current_address_id in (select student_id from student_enrolment where degree_program_id = 'Y') and state_province_county = "Nortucky"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.current_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.state_province_county = 'NorthCarolina' except select distinct t3.last_name from students as t3 join student_enrolment as t4 on t3.student_id = t4.student_id

column1: What are the last name of the students who live in North Carolina but have not registered in any degree programs?
column2: select last_name from students where current_address_id in (select current_address_id from students where date_first_registered = 'NC') except select t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.last_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.current_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.state_province_county = 'NorthCarolina' except select distinct t3.last_name from students as t3 join student_enrolment as t4 on t3.student_id = t4.student_id

column1: What is the date and id of the transcript with at least 2 courses listed?
column2: select t1.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcripts as t1 join courses as t2 on t1.course_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: What is the mobile phone number of the student named Timmothy Ward ?
column2: select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name = "Timmothy" and last_name = "Ward"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name = 'timmothy' and last_name = 'ward'

column1: Whose permanent address is different from his or her current address? List his or her first name.
column2: select distinct first_name from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.permanent_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: What is the first name of the student whose permanent address is different from his or her current one?
column2: select first_name from students where permanent_address_id not in (select permanent_address_id from students)
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select first_name from students where current_address_id!= permanent_address_id

column1: Which address holds the most number of students currently? List the address id and all lines.
column2: select t1.address_id, t1.line_1 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.address_id, t1.line_1, t1.line_2 from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id group by t1.address_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: When is the first transcript released? List the date and details.
column2: select transcript_date, other_details from transcripts as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select transcript_date, other_details from transcripts order by transcript_date asc limit 1

column1: How many times at most can a course enrollment result show in different transcripts? Also show the course enrollment id.
column2: select count(*), t1.course_id from courses as t1 join transcript_contents as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.student_course_id group by t1.course_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the maximum number of times that a course shows up in different transcripts and what is that course's enrollment id?
column2: select t1.course_name, count(*) from courses as t1 join student_enrolment_courses as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(*), student_course_id from transcript_contents group by student_course_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Show the date of the transcript which shows the least number of results, also list the id.
column2: select transcript_date, transcript_id from transcripts group by transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t2.transcript_date, t1.transcript_id from transcript_contents as t1 join transcripts as t2 on t1.transcript_id = t2.transcript_id group by t1.transcript_id order by count(*) asc limit 1

column1: Find the semester when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.
column2: select t2.semester_id from student_enrolment as t1 join semesters as t2 on t1.semester_id = t2.semester_id join courses as t3 on t1.course
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What is the id of the semester that had both Masters and Bachelors students enrolled?
column2: select semester_id from student_enrolment where student_id = "Masters" intersect select semester_id from student_enrolment where student_id = "Bachelors"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Master' intersect select distinct t2.semester_id from degree_programs as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.degree_program_id = t2.degree_program_id where degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column1: What are the different addresses that have students living there?
column2: select distinct t1.address_id from addresses as t1 join students as t2 on t1.address_id = t2.current_address_id
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select count(distinct current_address_id) from students

column1: What other details can you tell me about students in reverse alphabetical order?
column2: select other_student_details from students order by other_student_details
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select other_student_details from students order by other_student_details desc

column1: Find the first name of the students who permanently live in the country Haiti or have the cell phone number 09700166582 .
column2: select t1.first_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = "Haiti" or t1.cell_mobile_number = "09700166582"
column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name from students as t1 join addresses as t2 on t1.permanent_address_id = t2.address_id where t2.country = 'haiti' or t1.cell_mobile_number = '09700166582'

column1: List the area codes in which voters voted both for the contestant 'Tabatha Gehling' and the contestant 'Kelly Clauss'.
column2: select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.area_code = t2.vote_id join contestants as t3 on t2.contestant_number = t3.contestant_number where t3.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.area_code = t2.vote_id join contestants as t3 on t2.contestant_number = t3.contestant_number where t3.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'
column3: voter_1 | select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'

column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: Find the first names of owners living in Virginia and the names of dogs they own.
column2: select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.dog_id where t1.state = "Virginia"
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.first_name, t2.name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t1.state = 'Virginia'

column1: List the last name of the owner owning the youngest dog.
column2: select t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id order by t1.age asc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: Who owns the youngest dog? Give me his or her last name.
column2: select t2.last_name from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id order by t1.age asc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id where t2.age = ( select max(age) from dogs )

column1: How much does the most recent treatment cost?
column2: select max(cost_of_treatment) from treatments
column3: dog_kennels | select cost_of_treatment from treatments order by date_of_treatment desc limit 1

column1: List the dog name, age and weight of the dogs who have been abandoned? 1 stands for yes, and 0 stands for no.
column2: select name, age, weight from dogs where abandoned_yn = 1 and 0 = "no"
column3: dog_kennels | select name, age, weight from dogs where abandoned_yn = 1

column1: What are the dog name, age and weight of the dogs that were abandoned? Note that 1 stands for yes, and 0 stands for no in the tables.
column2: select name, age, weight from dogs where abandoned_yn = 1 union select t1.name, t1.age, t1.weight from dogs as t1 join owners as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.owner_id
column3: dog_kennels | select name, age, weight from dogs where abandoned_yn = 1

column1: How much does the most expensive charge type costs?
column2: select charge_type, max(charge_amount) from charges group by charge_type order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select max(charge_amount) from charges

column1: What is the charge amount of the most expensive charge type?
column2: select t1.charge_amount from charges as t1 join charges as t2 on t1.charge_id = t2.charge_id group by t2.charge_type order by sum(t2.cost_of_treatment
column3: dog_kennels | select max(charge_amount) from charges

column1: Show the property type descriptions of properties belonging to that code.
column2: select t1.property_type_description from ref_property_types as t1 join properties as t2 on t1.property_type_code = t2.property_type_code
column3: real_estate_properties | select t2.property_type_description from properties as t1 join ref_property_types as t2 on t1.property_type_code = t2.property_type_code group by t1.property_type_code
